Retired unbeaten boxing champion Floyd Mayweather says that when it comes to a possible big-money fight with Irish mixed martial arts star Conor McGregor, he is &#8220;out of retirement.&#8221;In a posting on the MMA website, the 40-year-old American said he wants to face McGregor, 28, in June.&#8220;For Conor McGregor, I&#8217;m coming out of retirement, just to fight Conor McGregor,&#8221; Mayweather told FightHype, according to the posting.&#8220;Today, I&#8217;m officially out of retirement for Conor McGregor. We don&#8217;t need to waste no time. We need to make this&#8230; happen quickly. Let&#8217;s get it on in June.&#8221;Mayweather had matched Rocky Marciano&#8217;s iconic 49-0 unbeaten career record when he walked away from boxing as the welterweight champion in 2015.Speculation of a Mayweather-McGregor fight has intensified in recent months, with the US star saying he is willing to meet McGregor in a boxing ring.McGregor, however, is under contract to the Ultimate Fighting Championship series, which would have to approve any deal for the bout to happen.&#8220;I don&#8217;t want to hear no more excuses about the money, about the UFC,&#8221; Mayweather said. &#8220;Sign the paper with the UFC so you can fight me in June. Simple and plain. Let&#8217;s fight in June. If you want to fight, sign the paperwork, let&#8217;s do it.&#8221;McGregor is on a break for the impending birth of his first child, a son with his long-time girlfriend Dee Devlin, who is due to give birth in May.